==English==

===Interjection===
[[tell]] [[me]] [[about]] [[it]]!
# (''ironic'') Don't tell me about it, the same thing is happening to me.

===Usage===
For this phrase to work, it must be said ironically

*''Old man who has lost his hair and hearing and use of his legs 1: "I've just lost my hair and hearing and use of my legs"
*Old man who has lost his hair and hearing and use of his legs 2: Yeah? Tell me about it''

